From the first case of COVID-19 pneumonia in Wuhan on December 8,2019, to the full outbreak on January 20,2020, the development of the situation is gripping everyone's heart.
It was a war that broke out at the beginning of the new year around every ordinary, ordinary Chinese.
This is our war, and we discuss it eagerly, analyze it carefully, deplore the loss of life in disaster, be moved by the audacity of the healer, and be Fear Is the Key by all human error, for all the little things we can do for them.
The Sea of life, let us hold hands in troubled times, and walk and cherish.

I thought December 30th would be an ordinary day -- colleagues in the office started discussing how to start the New Year Days in advance; "please be nice to me in 2020" was posted in Wechat's circle of friends. Maybe 2019 has been a tough year for a lot of people, and we laugh at ourselves but secretly hope that things will get better in the new year.
Early in the morning, I saw several screenshots and a voice sent by my good friend on Wechat. When I clicked on it, the voice was urgent: "Did you hear? SARS is making a comeback, right here in Wuhan! "
I froze, click on a few screen shots, the picture seems to be from the hospital's internal Doctor Group chat records, there is a suspected health commission issued an emergency notice. Back in 2003, when SARS hit, the three of us were juniors. Although the epidemic was mild in Wuhan at the time, the universities were still closed. When we came back from playing outside, we were caught by the school security guard. We cried our eyes out and begged the Dean to let us off the hook. Later, this thing was over, but the SARS, in my mind like a piece of white mist swamp, although do not want to close, but occasionally want to lift the veil to see.

Over the course of the day, we did not wait to dispel rumors, but more and more similar news, friends circle, wechat group, a variety of voices rushed out, let everyone doubt, and then heard that a group of experts came to Wuhan. The next afternoon, the government announced for the first time that seven of the 27 cases were in a serious condition. It investigated the south China Seafood City, saying that "no obvious human-to-human transmission was found and no medical staff infection was found" and that the condition could be prevented and controlled.
I was relieved when I read the news. It is thought that the government is quicker to respond, and not deliberately secretive -- a number that makes Florida an exception in a city of 14M.
Now that the government has stepped in, it should all be under control.

The South China seafood market is a comprehensive market. In addition to seafood, there are also specialized markets for fruits, beef and mutton, etc. . Things are fresh and cheap, which are very popular among local people. In the past, I also went there occasionally to buy some fruits wholesale, but I never quite liked the feel of it -- a huge market, with low houses built in unison, but with a dishevelled feel: boxes often piled haphazardly beside stalls, even by the side of garbage cans, the ground always has a puddle a puddle of sewage, a step on a foot of bad breath. As I passed the stalls, once my eyes stopped on the goods, I was grabbed by the hands of enthusiastic stall owners, who dragged me to the store with such enthusiasm that I felt I couldn't get away without buying three or four boxes of goods.
"Is there something wrong with the seafood? " I asked my colleague. He laughed. "You really don't know there are any wildlife in that market? "
"I hadn't really noticed. " I turned to the little girl in the same office. "So are you going to New Year's today? "
"Yes, why not? I already have an appointment with my boyfriend. " She laughed, "Just get ready. We're going to East L. , " she said, holding up a cotton mask she had worn to get to work each day since winter
Someone nearby asked her, "do you know 'sars' ? "
The little girl blinked: "Yes, how do not know. But then I was only 6 years old, too young to remember anything. "
I was a little worried. I called my younger sister, who is born in the 1990s, and asked her if she would cancel her New Year's Eve plans. She hesitated for a long time and replied, "yes, I will. " She added that she had originally proposed canceling the event, but her partner laughed at her "sparing her life. " "It's time to eat, it's time to play. How can you be a young man in a new age? "
Before hanging up the phone, she asked me: "This should be all right, I see the internet said all right. "
I hesitated and replied, "if it were me, I wouldn't go. I would advise you not to go, but you'd make up your own mind. "
Seriously, I'm scared to go back 17 years. Every time I think of the fear that once I breathed it in, I still get chills from the bottom of my heart. However, over the years, SARS for the post-90s is only a casual heard of the term, for or novelty-seeking or show-off game lovers, is also a flash in the past.

Now that I think about it, my fear came a few days before anyone else's. On the afternoon of January 16, my friend Zhang Lu called me with a nervous voice to tell me that something had happened at the home of a colleague at her company:

I asked him, "Do you know what we're going through right now? "
He curled his lips and began to look like a big boy. "Of course I know. I'm not an idiot. "
With that, he skipped off. As I watched him focus on his toys, I remembered that I had only taught him the right way to sneeze once, and he'd remembered to raise his little elbow every time since.
The child has grown up unexpectedly.
Maybe it's a threshold, and I don't want to talk about it with anyone else.

Epilogue

On the second day of the Lunar New Year, the first thing I did when I got up was to get in touch with Li Fei. She said that my temperature gradually dropped a little bit after taking the medicine, and my mood finally lightened a little.
On the fourth day of the siege, the initial panic and anxiety began to subside, and online discussion of the outbreak became less intense than in previous days.
More and more voices began to remind everyone to be rational, to be calm, fear. My mood is finally not like the last few days as anxious and helpless.
On the afternoon of the third day of the Lunar New Year, every wechat group began to turn a message, calling everyone to 8 pm, go to their own windows, through the window chorus "I and my motherland. ". Soon there were voices objecting to the spread of the virus and infection, but immediately someone said: "It doesn't matter, we wear masks to sing, we close the window to sing, we don't open our mouths, play the stereo. "
At eight o'clock, as night fell, I went out to the balcony, and for the first time in days, I took a serious look at the night scene. The lights on the opposite floor flicker, slowly count the past, the window lights are almost 2 / 3, and then look far, all the bright spots. It turns out there really are families like us who, for whatever reason, are staying here.
Whisper of the Heart, I really heard something. The lights go on and off, the songs come and go, like all our emotions these days.
This afternoon in the group to see the news, I also chuckled "naive" , but later in the circle of friends to see the singing video screen, I was surprised to produce a lot of moved.
There seemed to be some faint force in the shadowy voices, in the faces we had never met, that would have been broken in a second, but in a blink, a new courage had been born, and it was calming.

Those once secretly surging fear has been completely ignited, once a solid "nothing" bite out of more panic, everyone's anxiety seems to have reached the peak. Every group on Wechat is discussing where to sell face masks, how to wear them, and whether the sterilizer is useful, what are the symptoms of pneumonia... friends circle crazy people just in the Tianhe Airport transfer to stay for 2 hours back to sick, magic story spread, no one can tell us is true or false.
The Sky is overcast and the whole city is on tenterhooks.
On the morning of the 21st, I was awakened by the sound of my own terrible cough. My chest was gasping for air. Look at the time, 3:10. I sat up, filled with fear: AM I infected? It's not impossible, Florida -- how many high-risk things have I done in the past few days without thinking about it:
I went to see a movie, more than 100 people in the viewing hall full, a full 2 hours of viewing time, airtight environment, if there is an incubation period of infection how to do;
I went to eat a Japanese dish, claiming to eat raw hot spring eggs, I did not think to eat down;
A few days ago, a friend told me that a brand of clothing discount strength, I rushed to the weekend to buy, store crowded, Rub Shoulders;
These days I also several times in and out of the hospital, although the late wearing a mask, but sometimes will take off casually to a pocket a plug, and then took out and put on;
……
The more I thought about what I had done in the past 20 days, the more I panicked.
Husband asks, can be your psychological effect, nervous, so feel uncomfortable? I shook my head, as if I had no such reaction during the day, as if waking up in the middle of the night with a cough was not psychological but physical.
The husband showed a rare nervous look, stood up and turned out some medicine, let me eat first. Always resist to take medicine I obediently swallow the medicine, took a temperature, fortunately no fever. Afraid of infecting my husband, I put on a mask and lay down. Can Cough put on a mask to feel more relaxed breathing, I had to sit up again, half against the head of the bed, can not sleep late.
After I don't know how long, I finally lost myself and fell asleep. I woke up at 8 o'clock the next morning. My husband seems to have been up all night, half asleep and half awake, can feel him from time to time to touch my forehead.
When I got up, I went to the bathroom to wash my hair -- I was afraid if I had to go to the hospital, I wouldn't be able to do it for a long time. My husband stopped me in a hurry and asked me, "are you stupid? " , "washing your hair at this time will only increase the risk of illness. ". He lost his temper in a rare way and I had to let it go.

Every group on Wechat is discussing where to sell face masks, how to wear them, and whether the sterilizer is useful, what are the symptoms of pneumonia... friends circle crazy people just in the Tianhe Airport transfer to stay for 2 hours back to sick, magic story spread, no one can tell us is true or false.

The Sky is overcast and the whole city is on tenterhooks.

On the morning of the 21st, I was awakened by the sound of my own terrible cough. My chest was gasping for air. Look at the time, 3:10. I sat up, filled with fear: AM I infected? It's not impossible, Florida -- how many high-risk things have I done in the past few days without thinking about it:

I went to see a movie, more than 100 people in the viewing hall full, a full 2 hours of viewing time, airtight environment, if there is an incubation period of infection how to do;

I went to eat a Japanese dish, claiming to eat raw hot spring eggs, I did not think to eat down;

A few days ago, a friend told me that a brand of clothing discount strength, I rushed to the weekend to buy, store crowded, Rub Shoulders;

These days I also several times in and out of the hospital, although the late wearing a mask, but sometimes will take off casually to a pocket a plug, and then took out and put on;

……

The more I thought about what I had done in the past 20 days, the more I panicked.

Husband asks, can be your psychological effect, nervous, so feel uncomfortable? I shook my head, as if I had no such reaction during the day, as if waking up in the middle of the night with a cough was not psychological but physical.

The husband showed a rare nervous look, stood up and turned out some medicine, let me eat first. Always resist to take medicine I obediently swallow the medicine, took a temperature, fortunately no fever. Afraid of infecting my husband, I put on a mask and lay down. Can Cough put on a mask to feel more relaxed breathing, I had to sit up again, half against the head of the bed, can not sleep late.

After I don't know how long, I finally lost myself and fell asleep. I woke up at 8 o'clock the next morning. My husband seems to have been up all night, half asleep and half awake, can feel him from time to time to touch my forehead.

When I got up, I went to the bathroom to wash my hair -- I was afraid if I had to go to the hospital, I wouldn't be able to do it for a long time. My husband stopped me in a hurry and asked me, "are you stupid? " , "washing your hair at this time will only increase the risk of illness. ". He lost his temper in a rare way and I had to let it go.

Husband downstairs to buy medicine, a long time to come back, a box of hot online Lianhua qingwen capsules, a bottle of vitamin C chewable tablets. "How much? "

"No health insurance, only cash, even spend Qingwen more than 40, more than VC60! "

I was startled. "I thought we weren't going to raise the price. "

"Why do you care at this time? Get well first. "

I wear a mask 24 hours, as far as possible away from the husband and children, eating is also a one-time bowl chopsticks, with food a person to stand on the balcony window to eat. The heat and air conditioning were off, and I shivered by the window, not knowing whether it was cold or fear.

Some friends know I am not comfortable, some worry, hesitated to say should not go to the hospital to see? I thought about it: Never Mind, I might not be able to see it, I might catch it if I didn't have it, and then I looked at it as if it were a safe place in my mind, a sandcastle in the tide, in front of the randomness of life, could fall apart at any moment.

All along, my family has the habit of Spring Festival travel, years ago on a few days of annual leave, even the Spring Festival, just missed the peak period. This year because of the work plan adjustment, originally canceled travel arrangements, her husband suddenly brought up this matter: "Or, we still go out, no arrangements to go anywhere, to avoid the storm? "

I thought about it and shook my head. Husband also did not say anything more, we just gave up"escape Wuhan".

In the afternoon, the mobile phone received a push notice, announcing "from 26:00, the Wuhan Center, a total ban on motor vehicles. ".
A stone and stir up a thousand waves, unsurprisingly, the second round of supermarket panic-buying mini-surge immediately arrived. Friends Circle out of the endless reminder "XX supermarket do not go, " the supermarket shelves suddenly become empty, than the day of closure, more thorough and rapid.
The difference is that most of the people who went to the supermarket that day were parents. Today's wave is mostly young people who rely on private cars.
Trapped at home on the third day, originally disdained to store food, we suddenly felt a sense of urgency to save food for nothing. I recall my mother's retort when I used to laugh at her tendency to fill the fridge: Your generation has never felt the pinch of lack of food and clothing, so you can never feel the sense of security and awe that food brings to our generation.
I thought to myself, now I can finally understand.
I'm starting to wonder if I should go shopping again. Taking stock of the family's stock, rice and oil are almost at the bottom because they were not restocked last time. Vegetables and meat are only expected to be enough for two to three days. If we don't restock today, it will be a rainy day after the travel restriction tomorrow, how do we get the kids, the umbrella, and the heavy stuff back?
But if I go out now, I'll probably end up with empty shelves -- A friend sent me a video: People in the supermarket, waving their arms, not looking at what's on the shelves, not looking at the prices, just throw it in the cart.
I lost all courage in going out. Forget it. We'll figure it out when we run out of stock.
Later, however, the government issued an emergency notice to amend the restrictions.

In the early evening, the boy looked down from the balcony. After a while, he came bouncing in and told me, "mom, in the last five minutes, there have been three ambulances downstairs. "
I answered carelessly. He paused and asked earnestly, "is the situation serious now? "
I was shocked, I have always thought that 10-year-old he is just a child has not grown up, do not want to pass too much negative emotions to him. In addition to brief him about the situation, remind him to pay attention to hygiene, usually did not deliberately discuss the matter with him, I did not think, the child is not as heartless as I thought.
I asked him, "Do you know what we're going through right now? "
He curled his lips and began to look like a big boy. "Of course I know. I'm not an idiot. "
With that, he skipped off. As I watched him focus on his toys, I remembered that I had only taught him the right way to sneeze once, and he'd remembered to raise his little elbow every time since.
The child has grown up unexpectedly.
Maybe it's a threshold, and I don't want to talk about it with anyone else.

Epilogue

On the second day of the Lunar New Year, the first thing I did when I got up was to get in touch with Li Fei. She said that my temperature gradually dropped a little bit after taking the medicine, and my mood finally lightened a little.
On the fourth day of the siege, the initial panic and anxiety began to subside, and online discussion of the outbreak became less intense than in previous days.
More and more voices began to remind everyone to be rational, to be calm, fear. My mood is finally not like the last few days as anxious and helpless.
On the afternoon of the third day of the Lunar New Year, every wechat group began to turn a message, calling everyone to 8 pm, go to their own windows, through the window chorus "I and my motherland. ". Soon there were voices objecting to the spread of the virus and infection, but immediately someone said: "It doesn't matter, we wear masks to sing, we close the window to sing, we don't open our mouths, play the stereo. "
At eight o'clock, as night fell, I went out to the balcony, and for the first time in days, I took a serious look at the night scene. The lights on the opposite floor flicker, slowly count the past, the window lights are almost 2 / 3, and then look far, all the bright spots. It turns out there really are families like us who, for whatever reason, are staying here.
Whisper of the Heart, I really heard something. The lights go on and off, the songs come and go, like all our emotions these days.
This afternoon in the group to see the news, I also chuckled "naive" , but later in the circle of friends to see the singing video screen, I was surprised to produce a lot of moved.
There seemed to be some faint force in the shadowy voices, in the faces we had never met, that would have been broken in a second, but in a blink, a new courage had been born, and it was calming.
